HEADWORD: Surgical
<hw>Sur"gi*cal</hw> <pr>(s⟦ucir⟧r"j⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Of or pertaining to surgeons or surgery; done by means of surgery;
used in surgery; <as>as, a <ex>surgical</ex> operation;
<ex>surgical</ex> instruments</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Surgical fever</b></col>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<cd>Pyaemia.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>Traumatic fever, or the fever
accompanying inflammation.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

